	<td bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	<td class="subjectbar" height="20" style="font-size: 8pt;padding-left:10px;" width="100%">
		Future PvP server ruleset discussion

	</td>
	
		<td class="subjectbar" align=right style="padding:0px;padding-right:10px;">












		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 id="io_bpvpm3_table" 
		
			onClick="setId('3');showLiMenu(this,'io_bpvpm3','right',false);" 
			onDblClick="setId('3');showLiMenu(this,'io_bpvpm3','right',false);" 
			
		>
		<tr class=clickable>
			
				<td nowrap><a class=subjectbar_text style='font-size: 8pt;'>Options</a></td>
				
			<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
			<td><img src='/i/skins/default/button_options.gif' border=0 alt='Options' title='Options' width=11 height=28></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
		</table>
		
		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=2698'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#336600;'>Anarion77</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Journeyman<br>
			
				Posts: 68<br>
				
				Registered: 03-03-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=2698'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=3#M3">1</a> of 50
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1248 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV>I bought the game again to try out the Discord promotional server, and I'm still hoping that when the dust settles from the GoD launch there will be a new experimental&nbsp;ruleset server (as SOE has hinted). This thread is for the discussion of possible rulesets in a future PvP server. Because all the current PvP servers are so old, and because the game has proven to have such staying power, I think we can be optimistic that Sullon Zek won't be the last PvP server SOE ever tries. Below is my own proposal for a "PvP Classic Server." I invite your comments and criticism, and I also invite you to post other proposed PvP server rulesets here.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>PvP Classic Server</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A. Server is initially set up like Discord, with only Everquest Classic and the Legacy of Ykesha expansion active. Experience modifier is normal. After the server has been online 6 months, the Kunark expansion is activated and players can level past 50. After 1 year, Velious is added. At the 1 year, 6 month mark, all other expansions are activated. Since those of us arguing for a "Classic Server" can't seem to agree on which era of Everquest was the best (pre-Kunark, pre-Velious or pre-Luclin), this proposal gives everyone 6 months to enjoy the game as it was in those three stages.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>B. Death System: No permadeath -- with all the use of ShowEQ and client hacks on Discord, permadeath is not viable. Instead, players take experience from other players for a PvP kill equal to what they would get from a MoB of the same level. Players always respawn at their bind point with full gear, and a naked corpse is created in the case of a PvE death for resurrection purposes. This death system eliminates corpse camping and&nbsp;problematic corpse recoveries, which have been major customer service issues in the past. There is no coin or item loot.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>C. Binding is only allowed in cities for all classes. This reduces the advantage that binding classes have over mele classes and reduces bind rushing. PvP is unrestricted from level 14 to 50. There is no PvP for players under&nbsp;10 unless they enter a high level zone, in which case they lose their PvP immunity. By level 10, a player will have spent enough time on the server to make allies. This reduces newbie camping to a greater degree.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>D. Teams: The server will initially be divided into 9 city-state alliances. Cities with at least 8 available starting classes are a team unto themselves. The other teams consist of two allied cities, as explained in the backstory below. The story is set closer to the era of Everquest II, when Freeport has become an evil city and Qeynos is home of the good humans. Here's a breakdown of the teams and available classes:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1. Halas/Surefall: BST BER DRU RNG ROG SHM WAR <BR>2. Neriak: CLE ENC MAG NEC ROG SHD WAR WIZ <BR>3. Kaladim/Rivervale: BER CLE DRU RNG ROG PAL WAR <BR>4. Paineel/Oggok: BST BER CLE NEC SHD SHM WAR <BR>5. Erudin/Gukta: CLE ENC MAG PAL SHM WAR WIZ <BR>6. Ak'Anon: CLE ENC MAG NEC ROG SHD WAR WIZ <BR>7. Qeynos: BRD CLE ENC MAG MNK ROG PAL WAR WIZ <BR>8. Freeport: BRD CLE ENC MAG NEC ROG SHD WAR WIZ <BR>9. Kelethin/Felwithe: BRD CLE DRU ENC MAG RNG ROG PAL WAR WIZ </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Trolls will initially not be allowed on the server since this would add three more classes to the Neriak team, which is already&nbsp;the most attractive team. When Luclin and the other expansions are added, trolls will be activated in Neriak and available for play. Faction hits for PvP kills will be such that guards will agressively protect citizens of their city after only a few kills. There is no&nbsp;grouping, guilding, healing&nbsp;or buffing outside your team. When Kunark is activated, the Iksar will become the 10th team. When Luclin is activated, the Vah'Shir will become the 11th team.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>E. Scoring: A scoring system should be devised which ranks teams and guilds by kill ratio. At the end of the initial 6 months,&nbsp;guild and team winners will be declared.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>F. Backstory:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In a parallel world of Norrath, a terrible war is brewing as nine city-state alliances have formed to seek mastery over the known continents of Antonica, Faydwer and Erudin. Suspicion and hatred have turned old allies against each other, and only the bravest adventurers dare to journey outside the walls of their home city.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In Freeport, the Hall of Truth and the glorious Temple of Marr sit abandoned as the darker forces within the city have finally driven out the forces of light. The Ashen Order also lies abandoned as the followers of Quellious can no longer find tranquility in this corrupted city. Meanwhile in Neriak, the Thex monarchy laugh to themselves about the division of the foolish humans. With Freeport divided, the humans should present little threat to Neriak's ambitions for conquest. However, the troll slaves who arrived after the fall of Grobb have dwindled in numbers, and only a scattered few in the Foreign Quarter now remain. Neriak must rely upon its own Tier'Dal warriors on the front lines of the battles to come.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>On the other side of Antonica, the "good" humans have gathered together in Qeynos. However, their goodness is of a self-righteous sort, and all outsiders have been driven out. All half elves have been driven away to live in Surefall Glade, home of the distrusted rangers and druids, and the evil guilds of the Qeynos Catacombs lie abandoned as their numbers have been purged from the city with holy zeal.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Surefall Glade has become the home of the outcast half elves, who find themselves not only driven out by the humans of Qeynos, but also by the equally self-righteous wood elves and high elves of Faydwer. With allies so scarce, the denizens of Surefall Glade have carefully forged an alliance with the nature-loving barbarians of Halas, who are also despised by the zealots of Qeynos.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Meanwhile, on the continent of Erudin the ancient war between the cities of Erudin and Paineel rages on without relent. Seeking the upper hand, the devious masters of Paineel have summoned followers of Cazic Thule from the city of Oggok to swell their ranks. To counter this threat, the elders of Erudin have forged an alliance with frogloks of Gukta. The war among these deadly foes now spans across two continents.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And on the continent of Faydwer, bitter division has taken hold as three factions vie to rule the continent and eventually all of Norrath. The cities of Kelethin and Felwithe have purged themselves of the unpure blood of the half-elves, deeming them the foul children of despised humans. Those two cities stand together against the might of Ak'Anon, where the discipline of the paladin has been abandoned as the gnomes strive for power and dominance for their race. Beset by two such powerful enemies on their home continent, the dwarves of Kaladim have summoned aid from Rivervale and forged an alliance with that city. Only time can say which of these alliances will emerge victorious.</DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>03-26-2004</span> <span class=time_text>11:25 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
