		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<blockquote><hr>TolainDurant wrote:<br>I'de join a server like that in a heartbeat. make the teams hard coded so we don't have TZ/VZ syndrome<br><hr></blockquote><br>But I think there <i>would</i> be cross teaming on a server like this, even more so than what's happening now at the high levels on Sullon. If the play nice policy doesn't apply here - I assume it would be like Sullon, where training is legal - you'd have informal alliances between various teams in terms of training some opponents but not others, or even your own team (happens on Sullon, GMs really don't do much). With 9 and eventually 11, teams you'd have too many opportunities for ganging up on one team - as happened on Vallon and Tallon against the Darks. Sure, you couldn't group on this server, but you could all pick on the weakest team.  And what's going to happen to Lizards and Cats when those expansions open up in six months and a year?  It'll be a field day - All the Iksar will get up to whatever level they can in FoB, then go somewhere else and get whacked. <br><br>I dunno, I just don't think this would work. I think it would be better to have either two teams (Good and Evil) or three - Good, Evil, and Iksar.  Iksar would be a little weak - no Clerics, Bards, very little Crowd control - but it would at least be accurate in terms of Norrath's lore. And, with SKs, Necros and Shamans, they do have some of the best classes for PvPing. I'd give up Tallon or Vallon for this kind of server. Of course, I don't play on either of those two, so no big loss for me!	
		</td></tr>
