			>
			<DIV>Silenz have you done a breakdown of available classes for your teams? The only real problem I see with my teams is the fact that the half elf/barbarian team has no clerics. As far as making a good vs. evil server, that would be extremely boring to me. There just wouldn't be that much PvP, as in the early days on Sullon if you were evil. The idea of having 9 teams is that it garantees there will be plenty of conflict over hunting grounds.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as coding it to restrict the population of teams, they would never implement that. I actually considered it in an earlier draft of the above ruleset, but abandoned the idea when I realized how many complaints this would cause. Yes, one or two teams are inevitably going to have a numbers advantage. But with 9 teams, nobody is going to be able to level in the blue server safety that the evil team enjoyed on Sullon Zek.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Aenor the Betrayer</DIV>	
