<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=23#M23">13</a> of 50
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1083 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I have a fairly innovative solution(I'd like to think) on multiple team situation.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Stated in the original ruleset, scoring would be done using some sort of ratio system, I believe.&nbsp; I was just thinking, if these ratios are team specific, why not use them as a way to hardcode alliances?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For instance, say on a given day the Freeport team is hit hard by both the Qeynos team and the Neriak team.&nbsp; That would create a situation in which a large number of kills between the Freeport an Neriak teams as well as the Freeport and Queynos teams, while few kills between Qeynos and Neriak.&nbsp; The system could be programmed to recognize this occurance and could issue a coded alliance between the Qeynos and Neriak teams, in which grouping(though not guilding) would be temporarily allowed, and con message would change to amiable.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Similarly, cease-fires could be issued by the system in which con would change to indifferent or dubious&nbsp;and PK would not be allowed-though niether would grouping.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This system, which would function much in the way of&nbsp;team-wide faction,&nbsp;paired with a storyline randomizer(to keep certain alliances from becoming -too- stable) could provide a play enviroment with 3-5 "dynamic" alliances.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This approach also rectifies another problem: evaluating alliances.&nbsp; As con changes with conflict status, and assuming threatening is default for non team and ally is for same team, simply conning would reveal what team someone is on, much in the way it does on Sullon.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Finally, to address the obviousness of how the Ikkys and Cats would get slaughtered, it could be set up to where Kunark and Luclin are active, but "sealed" starting one month prior to allowing the entire server access.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
