		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Too bad SOE doesn't care about PvP.&nbsp; Sullon Zek was their last attempt at a special PvP ruleset server.&nbsp; It's pretty good, but they got a lot of holes they need to plug in order to make people want to play on it.</P>
<P>First off, evil team has the most one-shot "DT'ers".&nbsp; That alone makes Sullon Zek not balanced.&nbsp; In PvP, if you make a class able to do massive damage with 1shot/1cast/1hit, then you need to make sure that the class is available on all 3 teams.&nbsp; I think the deity based server like SZ is fun, things are more hardcoded making people have to work together if they are on the same team.&nbsp; Unfortunately the evil team rules, and they have locked it down so that no other teams can enter Elemental Planes...while they are working away at Plane of Time.&nbsp; Since EQ is so equipment dependent, you can see where I am going.</P>
<P>Second thing they need to change on a special ruleset server, is to make the res box stay for 10 seconds or less.&nbsp; Why?&nbsp; Because all people do now, instead of PvP, is to train with a res box.&nbsp; And since res boxes last so long, they can train in relative safety.&nbsp; In order for someone to die using a res box train, they'll have to be pretty stupid.&nbsp; Since SOE setup a special ruleset for SZ, I would suggest they further improve it by making res boxes last only 10 seconds on SZ.&nbsp; This will promote more PvP action, instead of a 1-man train that can crash the whole 50+ people raid.</P>
<P>I think if they made those 2 changes above, SZ will be a very good place to play on.&nbsp; But of course, that won't happen because SOE does not care about PvP.</P>
