			>
			A solution to this could be faction based teams. So every race/class combo would have its "starting" alignment.<br>I personally would really love a Light vs Dark server, or like on Sullon even a neutral team included. Good: All good fantasy races like Elves,Froglok, Vah Shir, Dwarves, Halflings. Neutral: Humans/Erudites/Barbs ( human races mind their own business ).Evil: the evil fantasy races. Now every player would have his "reputation" and this would determine his actual team. By killing players of other alignments and questing you could gain the faction needed even to change teams. To make it more realistic the different races could have different modifiers - which elf would trust a troll, eh? <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> And especially humans would have it easier to switch from neutral either to good or bad alignment while good and bad would have to do some serious questing at the beginning to change the team to ensure there are really only a few Dark Elves in the good team and only a few elves in the dark team. The more you switch the harder it gets and the higher the population of one team is the harder it gets to change to that alignment. Dont know how easy thats to implement/code but I think that server would rock especially since it could be a combination of a PvP and a roleplaying server.<br><br>Combine that with content for mass PVP (like conquering enemy towns temporarily to kill an NPC there for benefits for example, or having special items that improve your team in PvP and PvE or content only being accesseable if you control the majority of the items like in DAoC) and changes and balances to the resist system like mentioned in the other thread and a few more balance issues - voila there is a server that would prolly even attract "blue" players and would give players a reason not to play WoW <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>	
