<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=509#M509">25</a> of 50
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 692 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Sure, it has to be a solution that has maximum effect with minimum effort - it's meanwhile all about the money in the gaming industry like in every other business <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br><br>But honestly I don't know how hard it would be to code such a setup - thats a question only the Devs could answer. Still think that this setup creates a roleplaying promoting environment while also catering a good amount of the PvP players. And since a lot of players always demanded a roleplaying server this setup (if only few penalties for death like enhanced rezz effects and coin loss to prevent harassing) could attract players from non PvP servers. All it takes would be some advertisement -> for example a server history accesseable by everybody via webpage and events taking place. Too bad that EQ has mostly "static" content I'd always loved to see a MMORPG that develops over time and where you could be taking part in the changes that happen. And people could read the story of the server like reading a "Dragon Lance" book while the players would be the characters in that "online book" thats developing over time via events and consists in fact of a summary of those events. Yes I really think that such an online book combined with a few screenshots including a few massive fights for a town for example would be enough advertisement. To a small degree such a server history already exists since reputation is important on most PvP servers and so I remember for example the Grey Companions being a honourful guild with some intentions to roleplay and for sure remember guilds like the Prophets who wrote some part of the server history. And for sure most of the old school players remember even the "heroes" of the server that wrote server history ( like the term Blizzymodem <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> ), friends and enemies.	
		</td></tr>
